      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Limonene, a fragrant hydrocarbon found in lemons and oranges, is biosynthesized from geranyl diphosphate by the following pathway. Add curved arrows to show the mechanism of each step. Which step involves an alkene electrophilic addition? (The ion OP<sub>2</sub>O<sub>6</sub><sup>4−</sup> is the diphosphate ion, and “Base” is an unspecified base in the enzyme that catalyzes the reaction.)</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb0FhIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--770ad20976a14c4ba2b3f9716f777f1f3bf7af43/OSX_OrgChem_07_99_Geranyl_img.jpg\" alt=\"A 3-step biosynthesis reaction shows the formation of limonene from geranyl diphosphate.\">",
